org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.anonymizer.dicom

Class DICOMAnonymizer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.anonymizer.dicom.DICOMAnonymizer

  • public class DICOMAnonymizer
extends java.lang.Object
    The MIRC DICOM anonymizer. The anonymizer provides de-identification and re-identification of DICOM objects for clinical trials. Each element as well as certain groups of elements are scriptable. See the RSNA MIRC Wiki for more more information.

      • anonymize

        public static AnonymizerStatus anonymize(java.io.File inFile,
                         java.io.File outFile,
                         java.util.Properties cmds,
                         java.util.Properties lkup,
                         IntegerTable intTable,
                         boolean forceIVRLE,
                         boolean renameToSOPIUID)
        Anonymizes the input file, writing the result to the output file. The input and output files are allowed to be the same. The fields to anonymize are scripted in the properties file.

        Important note: if the script generates a skip() or quarantine() function call, the output file is not written and the input file is unmodified, even if it is the same as the output file.

        Parameters:
        inFile - the file to anonymize.
        outFile - the output file. It may be same as inFile if you want to anonymize in place.
        cmds - the properties object containing the anonymization commands.
        lkup - the properties object containing the local lookup table; null if local lookup is not to be used.
        forceIVRLE - force the transfer syntax to IVRLE if true; leave the syntax unmodified if false.
        renameToSOPIUID - rename the output file to [SOPInstanceUID].dcm, where [SOPInstanceUID] is the value in the anonymized object (in case it is remapped during anonymization.
        Returns:
        the static status result
